The government wants the torture of "witches" and issued a brochure,
Women who are branded as witches in Burkina Faso, usually some common social characteristics.
They are part of the older generation, they cannot find work - for example, for health reasons, they are single and have no children.
If one of these women to witch "will", will be isolated, so that they can be dangerous for the rest of the village.
"Men are affected by this fate quite rare."
"The young and healthy women this, since they are at work and help" describes a sister describes the situation in the capital of the West African state of Burkina Faso in a Spezialheim by more than a hundred women who were expelled from their communities.
The local government decided, against these abnormal "social action".
And for this reason, a brochure, the "witch hunt".
The issue has a downside.
"More than 70 percent of all adults in Burkina Faso cannot read" said the newspaper "the standard" to the dilemma of the written information.
To be accused of witchcraft is, but also in other African countries.
In the neighbouring country of Burkina Faso, Ghana, the 27 - year-old Ammy Hemmahová of three women and two men to death - they doused with kerosene and set them.
About this incident, including the BBC server.
The perpetrators claimed, however, The matter would have been only a combination of unfortunate circumstances.
Their version that was inflamed oil, which will be used for ritual Salbungen.
And, after the group, "an evil spirit" from "good health".
The isolation of "witches" support the people here without regard to their education.
"The standard quoted a 42 - year-old entrepreneur from Burkina Faso:" Fresserinnen human souls are used as a threat, "he said.
While the government in Burkina Faso, at least tried to defuse the witch-hunt that has mitgemischt the gambianische President last year, the President himself.
"President Yahya Jammeh revived after the death of his aunt, a monstrous witch hunt, because they had the death and would try to kill the president himself by black magic."
"He called shaman from nearby Guinea to aid, accompanied by police officers, soldiers and the bodyguard of President indiscriminately arrested men and women from villages gambianischen kidnapped and brought to the farm in Kanilai", the organisation Amnesty International in its report.
On the farm were forced from prison people to drink an Absud from plants with halluzinogener effect, but also the bowel and kidney problems.
Two of the arretierten people survived not stay on the farm.
It was on the basis of international pressure were released nearly a thousand prisoners.
