The architects saw a - the office is also a nursery
The office buildings Avriopoint in Brno is the new headquarters of the company arch. Design.
But who would expect a mini nursery, with all that entails: colourful walls, creative furniture, toys and even a mini playground on the outside terrace.
This nursery is since last year, the staff of arch. Design available.
The study and architecture office arch. Design, whose Ateliers a number of prominent Brünner buildings, from the first drafts of the new building Avriopoint with the premises for his firms mini nursery.
Prescient, because most of its 90 staff (interior) are in the baby boom ages and the company is keen that the Projektantinnen and Architektinnen as quickly as possible.
Together with the possibility of shortening working, the nursery is another bonus, has to offer the arch. Design its employees in the concept of social program.
The Bauingenieurinnen and architektinnen have it easier, demanding their profession and child care.
The mini nursery is an original idea of the staff of arch. Design and with the support of the management them financial assistance from the European Union and of the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs for their project.
The occupational mini nursery is financed by the operational programme, human resources and employment policy from the European Social Fund and the state of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to this funding (grants of $2, 8 million CZK) could be obtained the necessary facilities and equipment and for the duration of 2 years for qualified staff and for the operation.
After the absorption of funds (2 years) is committed to the society arch. Design to operate the mini nursery 3 more years at their own expense.
The preparation of this project, a year, and the society economy rating in the of effective aid.
The children Subcontinent qualified staff - a nurse and a kindergarten lesson Rin, the kindergarten children can visit without altersmäßige restrictions, although most of them are about three years old.
And because it is a mini nursery, at the same time, only 5 children, however, the day on several children each other.
The nursery operation is flexible to the needs of parents, the children of all staff have in relation to the use of the nursery equal rights, regardless of the corporate hierarchy and their position.
Although individual education and care, the programme content in the mini nursery nevertheless comparable with the framework programme of pre-school education.
The children are not only, in particular, are excellent teaching - ranging from basic knowledge to pre-school education, by The way they learn English.
The classroom is not only with toys and creative games, but also with a computer, the children.
What is more, the presence of small children in the company contributes to a friendly and positive business environment.
The parents can always look at the children and so the stress in the late collection of children from a faraway kindergarten.
The parents use their working time more productive.
No wonder that natural and loyal employee relations.
Arch. Design introduced under the Czech firms, which provide for the recruitment of new staff clear Benefits, family-friendly and encourage such programmes through their staff marketing.
A bone House fascinated even after 100 years. If you look at the Interieure of Gaudi to
The roof seems to be the backs of prehistoric Echse, as the vertebral column of a Dinosauriers the stairs and the Balkone are past Fischmäuler.
This is the Casa Batlló of Catalan architect Antonio Gaudi in Barcelona.
The local inhabitants of the house, with its organic forms the nickname "bones".
Organic forms, wild colors, the unusual use of stone, Kachelsplittern and mosaic, the scales, facades and ubiquitous soft lines, all this are standard features for the youth of Antonio Gaudi.
The facade of the House plays with beautiful lines, lack force paints and Texturen, the natural and life.
Only on closer inspection you observe that everything from geometry, rhythm and thoughtful.
In the night, the whole façade of plastic, dramatic and the special Anleuchtung reinforces the luster of colors.
The same dynamic lines and tortuous forms dominate the interior of the house.
Waves of well-formed wood copied the window frames, parapets, Zierelemente by doors, even Guck holes and trade.
The house Batlló in the quarter Eixample in the busy shopping street Passeig de Grácia No 43 was created by converting a house in 1877, said the architects Emilio Sala Cortese.
The reconstruction took two years and was completed in 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrialists Josep Batlló, was originally on the demolition of the old and the construction of a completely new building, but eventually he agreed to the idea Gaudís on an unusual and cheaper, too.
The rental house Casa Batlló Antoni Gaudí, however, is not alone.
He worked with the architect Josep Maria Jujol together.
On the drawing board take away for the representative of the realities owner and the use of mosaics of the facade was his idea.
In the design of the facade, but also many other Bildner and artists.
The joint work on the drafts of the Casa Batlló was the beginning of a fruitful cooperation of Jujola and Gaudí.
So Jujol was also involved in the construction of Gaudís house Casa Milá in the park Güell where other works of Antoni Gaudí.
Shortly after its completion, the house of the local inhabitants of organic forms the nickname "bones".
Others described it the specific Fensteröffnungsmechanismus due to the "yawning house".
It also says that at the top of the building is the sword of Saint George, the barons of Catalonia.
But also other bildhauerische elements of a hidden religious motives.
Gaudí devised for the House, for the time Zentralheizungssystem with unique ventilation channels and typical Kaminen.
Something seems bizarre their propensity to 45 degrees.
When he ignored Gaudí consistently all the building codes and could not be led astray.
Before construction - he of the city's planning permission, but the claims made about the planned reconstruction were so vague that the city fathers two years later, the completion of the result that they demanded.
The gentlemen of the Council, among other things, that the building with its pillars in the public sidewalk.
The changes, there was no longer, however, quite the contrary - only fifteen days after the invitation of the urban community, Josep Batlló submitted an application for approval of the rental of the two höchstgelegenen floors of the House - and they gave him promptly.
The homeowners themselves, in the lower floors.
In the gallery in the 2th floor was a social showroom, in the third floor of the bedroom and private rooms of the house.
The ground floor was leased to a jeweller business.
The whole sechsstöckige buildings going up the stairs to the roof terrace.
All the main elements of the new right-wing corner and precise lines removed and replaced by bent and geschwungene walls.
Gaudí worked but also with a modern approach to mutual combination of rooms.
The social part is by opening the showroom doors completely and while a larger society without having to take vertraulicheren talks on a certain intimacy.
The house was given by Gaudís reconstruction apart from a new facade was also a very unusual roof and two other floors.
Impressively is also Gaudís game with the light and the blue and white glasierten Kacheln, which is dressed in the courtyard and the light.
The game of these two colours gives all floors of the House a maximum light.
He made the principle that reflects the white light better than dark colours, which absorb sunlight, on the contrary.
The House Casa Batlló, which was included in the world heritage list of Unesco, can visit today everyone.
The first floor is the geräumigste and prächtigste housing made available to the public.
The homeowners determined in the years to this step and that on the occasion of the 150. geburtstags of the famous Creator.
After it was discovered that this is a very profitable business, it has maintained the surveys, and extended to other common and the attic rooms, including the roof terrace.
The price to visit the monument is no trifling matter, he is 16.50 EUR, students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourists cards received 20 percent reduction.
This amount exceeds the entry prices to other Gaudí buildings in the city.
Anyone who wants to learn the real atmosphere of the House, with its Drachentürmchen should try to close friendship with one of the inhabitants and visit him at home.
