Both police and the state security Service, high protection money, so that they can keep their standard of living in Moscow, it says.
They collect money not only legitimate business, but also by organized criminal gangs.
Each layer of bureaucracy - Prime Minister Vladimir Putin has described as "vertical of power" - takes its part of the money that moves up the ladder.
The memo, which was sent under the name of John Beyrle ambassador to Washington, was published on Tuesday by WikiLeaks published on its website.
The memo is based on sources, whose names have been edited.
It was written, while Yuri Luzhkov, Moscow's Mayor, and accused him of corruption.
In the meantime, He was fired by President Dmitry Medvedev in October, but there is little evidence that would have been sorted out.
Luzhkov and his wife, Yelena Baturina, who owns a construction company, known for years have rejected accusations of corruption, and he has won numerous libel against such accusations.
