A source, is, "said that Moscow's business owners understand that it is best to the protection of the FSB and MVD (and not by organised crime), because they are not only more weapons, resources and power than the criminals, but also because they are protected by law."
"This is why not ask the protection by criminal gangs as before."
The memo noted that, while the collection of funds, the protection of very modest, no; even those who pay, are sometimes arrested.
Those who do not pay, closed their business very quickly - on the basis of one or other Vorwands.
Medvedev has spoken on several occasions, to combat corruption, said that he has made little progress.
The memo contains descriptions of men who with suitcases, who were probably full of money, in the Kremlin.
"In his fight against corruption must rely on the bureaucrats" said Georgy Satarov, director of by, a Moscow think tank, in a recent interview.
"But it is part of the bureaucracy."
"It is not part of the political class, because there is not a political class in Russia."
Without politicians, without opposition, without a separation of powers, he says, corruption is inevitable.
Nationwide, by the corruption, costing more than $300 billion per year.
