Zapatero and the red line of Germany
Berlin has opted for the keeping the EUR, but at the same time, conditions for the whole of the European Union.
The tension on the markets have triggered a two-fold response from the government.
On the one hand, has produced José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero new adaptation measures, ranging from tax reductions for small and micro enterprises, the regulation of temporary work agencies or the lifting of the EUR 426 of support for the unemployed, not unemployment benefits, to the privatisation of 49 percent of AENA, the management of airports and El Prat and 30 percent of the state lottery.
On the other hand, supports the deputy leader, Elena Salgado, with the help of former Prime Minister Felipe González criticism of Chancellor Angela Merkel as the person responsible for the current crisis herausbeschwört.
How to understand these events?
It is anticipated that Merkel's position is no fault of their public relations.
On the contrary, it is a new round in the difficult process of redefining the EUR.
It is Germany a fundamentally new perspective to shape our future, with the maintenance of the old traditions of much of its partners.
In the face of resistance in Europe begins to spekuliern in Germany on three possible ways out of the crisis.
The first, a strong EUR with Germany, austria, the Netherlands and other countries, while the south to leave the EUR area.
Second: the reintroduction of the Deutsche Mark - though it sounds like science fiction - supported by a majority of public opinion, approximately 50 percent of the population.
The third: a restructuring of the EUR under German proposals. This means: more macroeconomic control; strict financial management; penalties for countries that exceed the targets; möglichereweise the default of certain countries, as well as the extension of the costs of potential measures to the private sector.
The German position is clear and has been for some time. Therefore, there is now no excuses.
First, in 2009, when both the IMF and the European Commission incentives for deficits and the German government came up with a constitutional reform, in order to prevent this from 2016.
It was the first signs of the polarisation between what Germany (strict fiscal plans and stable public finances) and the practices of its European partners, including France.
The second sign, the Central European country, as hinausschob Merkel's decision to rescue Greece.
At that time was heavily criticised. But the fact is that the political consensus in Germany, the public and published opinion totally opposed to a bailout of Greece.
Finally, Merkel in recent days of October with a clear position. It calls for a reform of the European Union, in order to facilitate the rescue of a country and at the same time, the private lenders to pay a portion of the costs.
This position has been interpreted as anti-European, since the Ireland crisis and everything.
But their proposal, if somewhat sweetened, was adopted. In the coming months we will be in the reform of the European union, these measures from 2013 to participate.
Germany has drawn a red line, not to exceed.
It says all that - even if It must be taken now unpopular measures - there will be no of this date the functioning of the EUR.
2013 will be the year of birth of a new monetary area, in which the offending countries be severely punished, may be forced to declare itself insolvent and, in this case, the private sector must play a part of the costs.
Germany shows us that we must take a strong growth rate, high savings and investment rates, moderation in consumption, improving productivity and competitiveness and positive external balances.
The alternative, which is based on debt and construction with huge holes in the balance of payments, as she was led by Spain in boom times, will not be tolerated.
The offer is clear.
And we would do poorly, not to understand it.
It is not only about runterzufahren the government deficit by the year 2013 to three percent.
The demands are much tougher.
And the worst thing we could do under these conditions, is to cheat ourselves.
I hope that the current turbulence in more calm.
And the opportunities that will be offered, And will use the spring of 2013.
It seems that Zapatero, and his double announcement (the promised reforms after the meeting with the large companies last Saturday and yesterday's announcement of new measures yesterday) points out that, despite the criticism of Merkel's hypothesis, to their own house in order, had their way.
But the Germany of red line is there, and it does not seem that would change.
Among the possibilities is that we should leave the countries with little serious cramped EUR area, cannot be ruled out.
In this case could say Germany still, it warned.
Sport and usually bypassing
Tricks like Alonso and Ramos in the game against the Ajax show inventiveness, but not the desire to avoid a sanction.
The alleged by two players of Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos), launched in the game of 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League meant that much ink has been spilled about whether it is an unsportliche act or not and whether it should be sanctioned possibly both players by UEFA.
As is well known, the two players lost a few minutes (her team had already clearly) time and played several fouls, so that the referee showed them the second yellow card.
In this way, would give the Real Madrid and his group, the two players the sanction next League game against the Auxerre meet and without cards in the next phase of the game.
Finally, punished the Disciplinary Committee of the UEFA club's coach, José Mourinho, with two games and the players involved with different sums of money.
The provocation of a yellow card under these or similar circumstances is not a new practice, it is more often in the world of football.
It is so widespread that they are part of the ethos - the unwritten, but in this sport followed rules - is.
Part of the debate about the case that a team of football clubs Real Madrid (in his anthem precious courage and honour and on other occasions his players for similar incidents had punished) played the main role, and the proportion of Mourinho, the episode has added a more to its long history as theatralischer and provocative technicians.
In any case, the debate about whether this is not explicitly prohibited by the statutes behaviour contradicts the principles of sport, that is to say whether these acts of circumvention rule. Indeed, this approach to the statutes of the sport, but seem to circumvent its meaning.
In this matter should be examined In the spirit of sport.
The sporting spirit defended the physical integrity of the opponent, an aspect that was not threatened by these actions, because it was not an aggressive game.
Another aspect of a clean game is to prevent the offending players an unfair advantage from the opposing team. That did not happen.
The paradox is the act of players of Real Madrid, that they do not correspond to what we normally under false game or rule, because the way in which the rule was not secretly, in order to avoid a penalty, but they should be as visible as possible, so that they will be punished by the referee.
The players and the sanction happily.
Another question is, what kind of advantage the offender from the deliberate fouls.
It should be emphasised that the rival in a disadvantageous position were still erheischt advantages for the feigned game, was the obvious result of this action was that their team played out with fewer players.
It is also an useful strategy for the next game, because the club is not about these players.
The advantage is that the player the next phase of the Champions League without cards, which could threaten their participation in a future game.
But it is a long-term, up to a certain degree of uncertainty, which could leave the team at some point. Moreover, the players with this approach a sanction and go in the second cycle of cards, the accumulation of cards with a card less than in the first cycle.
It is not clear whether it really is an advantage.
Ultimately, such practices against the spirit of sport, including strategic decisions, in order to derive maximum benefit from the regulations.
In this case the players wanted no sanction (that would be a clear case of circumvention rule), they wanted more, when they do this.
They took a strategic decision, without a penalty or to flee before her.
Although the border between imagination and regulatory environment, I believe that this matter is a clear case of inventiveness.
I have the impression that the controversy has arisen as a result of two factors: because there are two exclusions and because of the nature of the Regelübertragung provoked.
The damage was caused to the principles of sport through these actions, is less ethical than aesthetic.
