China has maintained its targets to reduce greenhouse gases,
The representative of China stated on the COP16, his country has made enormous efforts to reduce carbon footprints and it would maintain its offer to 2020 40 to 45 percent of greenhouse gases.
China considers his offer to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases by 2020 to 40 to 45 percent, Su Wei, the representative of the country on the COP16.
In his first public appearance at the 16th world climate summit COP16 (United Nations), Su Wei, his country had made enormous efforts to reduce the carbon traces and convert its industry.
He said that his country in the last four years have invested $245 million $s in order to reduce the emission of greenhouse gases.
However, he said that China would not change its objectives, but would work together with the international community on this matter.
He said that the Chinese unterteile strategy on climate change in four aspects: dialogue, capacity building, institution building and support of pilot programmes.
We have made progress In all aspects, including the adoption of a new energy bill last year, which meant the targets for reducing the emission of greenhouse gases, he said.
On the other hand, he stressed that in China the authorities of the states with the central government and local authorities to achieve the objectives of energy saving, the efficient use of energy and to achieve the reduction of emissions.
In addition, he said, have been taken or completed some multiannual plans, both those who have been funded by the Chinese government, as well as those that received the money from other countries.
For example, he was referring to the programme for Effective use of energy, which was introduced in the last five years and investment by the United Nations (un), the government and private hands.
It is also a project at the provincial level on climate change, another exchange of traditional incandescent light bulbs by the householder and another for mitigation and adaptation, he said.
Martin Krol government, scientific adviser on climate change in this country, confirmed that the efforts of China would be far greater than is commonly believed.
He showed that China's per capita greenhouse gas emissions in China six tonnes per person, while it is in the United States 100 tonnes. China is for a neunprozentigen overall contribution to environmental pollution.
Similarly, there is progress in the field of energy use. the energy efficiency has increased in the last five years, twenty percent and by the year 2020 is a further, he said.
