The U.S. does not change the rules for obtaining a visa
The people must be her audience with the consulate in the service visa applications; costs will be waiting times.
From 10 January 2011 to change the procedures for applying for a visa in the United States Embassy and the consulates.
Most of the new procedure, the applicants before their meeting at the consulate in the service visa applications (ASC, the initials in English).
The staff of the ASC, the biometric data on the applicant, which will be reviewed by the consulate in the conversation.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the hopefuls, including:
The total cost of the visa, because there is no longer needed the deadline, the processing of visa applications and the transportation service, with the document, to pay.
The applicant is only one payment, which covers the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the Gegenwerit to $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for a visa application (including visas for temporary workers) and $390 for Händer and investors.
Those who want to extend their visas only to have a conversation at the consulate, they only have to imagine the nearest ASC, where they and their fingerprints.
Since the biometric data in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the meeting at the consulate in less time than before.
Those who refuse a visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey, Nuevo Laredo, do not have to pay the service surcharge of $26.
